,"1416":"1416","1405":"1405","Muscry, Ireland":"Ireland","Ireland":"Ireland","Muskerry, Cork, Ireland":"County Cork, Ireland","Cork, County Cork, Ireland":"Cork, County Cork, Ireland","Cork, Cork, Ireland":"Cork, County Cork, Ireland","Carbery, Kildare, Ireland":"Carbury, County Kildare, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"McCarthy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Donal, Liam, Cormac, Niall, Aileen, Brigid, Conor, Declan, Dermod, Dermot, Finbar.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cárthaigh</b> ‘son of <i>Cárthach</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘loving’. This was the name of a ruling family in Munster. In Ireland major branches were distinguished by the following epithets: <i>mór</i> ‘great’ in Kerry, <i>riabhach</i> ‘brindled’ in Carbery, west Cork."],"variants":[{"name":"McArthy","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cárthaigh</b>, ‘son of <i>Cárthach</i>’. See   McCarthy  ."]},{"name":"McCarty","meanings":["Irish: variant of   McCarthy  , reflecting the common southern Irish pronunciation of <i>th</i>."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Ellen McCarthy was born in 1416, in Cork, County Cork, Ireland as the daughter of Teige MacCarthy 6th Lord of Muskerry and Catherine O'Brian. She married Demond-an-Dunaidh MacCarthy Reagh 7th Prince of Carbery in 1452, in County Cork, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1460, in her hometown, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1416–1460":"1416–1460","1413–1451":"1413–1451","1415–1494":"1415–1494","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1410–1473":"1410–1473","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1448–1480":"1448–1480","1458–Male":"1458–Surnud","–1461":"–1461","1385–1428":"1385–1428","1385":"1385","1440":"1440","1473":"1473","1451":"1451","1461":"1461","1494":"1494","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1448":"1448","1415":"1415","1458":"1458","1413":"1413","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1452":"1452","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1428":"1428","1505":"1505","1416":"1416","1405":"1405","Muscry, Ireland":"Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Muskerry, Cork, Ireland":"County Cork, Iirimaa","Cork, County Cork, Ireland":"Cork, County Cork, Iirimaa","Cork, Cork, Ireland":"Cork, County Cork, Iirimaa","Carbery, Kildare, Ireland":"Carbury, County Kildare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1416–1460":"1416–1460","1413–1451":"1413–1451","1415–1494":"1415–1494","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","1410–1473":"1410–1473","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1448–1480":"1448–1480","1458–Male":"1458–Kuollut","–1461":"–1461","1385–1428":"1385–1428","1385":"1385","1440":"1440","1473":"1473","1451":"1451","1461":"1461","1494":"1494","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1448":"1448","1415":"1415","1458":"1458","1413":"1413","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1452":"1452","about 1440":"noin 1440","1428":"1428","1505":"1505","1416":"1416","1405":"1405","Muscry, Ireland":"Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti","Muskerry, Cork, Ireland":"County 